<dl id="n11134b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11134b">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11134b"> 134(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> replied in these words / skinsail shift</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Une nuit, &agrave; la clart&eacute; de la lune, tandis que tous les Natchez dorment au fond de leurs pirogues, et que la flotte indienne, &eacute;levant ses <mark>voiles de peaux de b&ecirc;tes</mark>, fuit devant une l&eacute;g&egrave;re brise, Ren&eacute;, demeur&eacute; seul avex Chactas, lui demande le r&eacute;cit de ses aventures. Le vieillard consent &agrave; le satisfaire, et assis avec lui sur la poupe de la pirogue, il commence <mark>en ces mots</mark>: <br><font color="green">[One night, in the moonlight, while all the Natchez slept in their canoes, and the Indian flotilla, raising its sails of animal skins, fled before a light breeze, Ren&eacute;, alone with Chactas, asks him to tell of his adventures. The old man agrees to satisfy his wishes, and seated with him in the stern of the canoe, begins in these words]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Atala</i> 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
